{
  "stem": "3964.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was bar mitzvahed in April of 1938, which obviously was before the Kristallnacht affair.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "By that time, the Jewish community had-- which I mentioned earlier-- was 16 families-- had depleted to a large degree.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I believe 8 of the families, of the 16, had left Gemunden-- either had immigrated to the United States, South Africa, Argentina, and/or moved into larger cities away from Gemunden, because they didn't want to be exposed to the horrors which were going on in-- in Gemunden itself.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And out of the other eight families, four of them were single, older women with their daughters, living in their houses in Gemunden.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So consequently, there was not a minyan available anymore.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But there were several smaller cities-- smaller villages, within, I would say, about five or six kilometers around Gemunden, which still had Jewish people living there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Most of them were farmers, or they were cattle dealers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They bought and sold cows and horses to the farmers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they would come on Shabbat for minyan to Gemunden, because we didn't have a minyan in Gemunden anymore, obviously.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And for my bar mitzvah, we had a full house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I believe there must have been possibly 20 men, 25 maybe-- including my father's family, who did not live in Gemunden-- had come from-- from the southern part of Germany to visit and celebrate the bar mitzvah with us together.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a normal affair, as normal as it could have been in 1938, prior to the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It's still in my memory.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I have not talked about it much, but it was a wonderful experience for me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Number one, I studied very hard.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
